2026-03-29T12:59:48.6300367Z             "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- **Per-customer email settings**: Added customer-level overrides for summary window offset, window size, window count, and latest-locations toggle. Consolidated the admin Detail page from multiple separate update forms into a single unified settings form.\r\n- **Zigbee connectivity monitoring**: Added polling of the Hue `/resource/zigbee_connectivity` endpoint alongside battery. Unreachable devices are now displayed in the admin portal and included in summary emails.\r\n- **Fixed device type model**: Previously, each Hue service endpoint (motion, temperature, battery, connectivity) created separate Device rows for the same physical device. Now one Device row per physical device, with DeviceType derived from the device's `services[]` array (matching the Hue CLIP v2 resource model). Stale device removal is a single pass that only runs when all endpoints are polled.\r\n- **Database migration**: Added `AddCustomerEmailSettings` migration for the new per-customer fields (`SummaryWindowOffsetHours`, `SummaryWindowHours`, `SummaryWindowCount`, `IncludeLatestLocations`).\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Worker/Services/PollingService.cs` — One Device row per physical device; device type from services array; unified stale removal; Zigbee connectivity polling\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Core/Constants/DeviceTypes.cs` — Removed `Battery`/`ZigbeeConnectivity` (service types, not device types); added `Unknown`\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Core/Constants/ReadingTypes.cs` — Added `ZigbeeConnectivity`\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Core/Interfaces/IHueApiClient.cs`, `Services/HueApiClient.cs` — New `GetZigbeeConnectivityAsync` method\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Core/Models/HueApiModels.cs` — Added `HueZigbeeConnectivityResource` model\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Data/Entities/Customer.cs` — Per-customer email setting fields\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Data/Migrations/` — `AddCustomerEmailSettings` migration\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Admin/Pages/Customers/Detail.cshtml[.cs]` — Unified settings form; unreachable device display; battery/connectivity queries by reading type\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Email/EmailRenderer.cs` — Connectivity status in emails; per-customer settings support\r\n- `tests/` — Updated tests across all three test projects (551 total, all passing)\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n- [ ] Verify `dotnet build` and `dotnet test` pass (all 551 tests)\r\n- [ ] Confirm admin Detail page shows battery status and unreachable devices\r\n- [ ] Verify per-customer email settings (window size, count, offset, latest locations) can be edited and persist\r\n- [ ] Check that polling creates one Device row per physical Hue device (not per service type)\r\n- [ ] Confirm stale device removal only runs during battery poll cycles\r\n- [ ] Verify mains-powered devices (no battery) get connectivity readings but no battery readings\r\n\r\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01Gmjk912cuixJo7D9UqZQGA",
